begin_memory_text: We talked about the quality of our devices, where we were from, our names, she has kids. We talked about goats. I talked about veterinary care.
middle_memory_text: She asked if goats actually eat everything. I explained no they do not. Then she asked about crops and I talked about my kitchen garden and a pasta sauce I invented.
end_memory_text: I told her the book I am writing, how the bad guy inspired the pasta sauce. I gave her a synopsis of the story including the end. We signed off.
rest_of_day_open: Tomorrow morning I am going to butcher out a sheep with some family friends. I will spend the rest of the week recovering from socializing. I am an extreme introvert, so no matter how much I like the visits, conversations exhaust me. I will most likely do some streaming and hopefully get some writing done.
critical_positive: We were two women from texas who were forced into conversation. I think she is a bit younger than I am, but we were able to find common ground. And she asked me a question about my livestock, specifically goats, which got the ball rolling. It was an easy transition to talk about turkeys and snakes and the book I am writing.
critical_negative: From my end, everything worked well. I learned she has children, does home schooling, lives in texas, is married, hates snakes, and is creeped out by holes. She learned I am an introvert, asked good questions, and seemed interested in livestock. I don't think anything went poorly. I also think she or a family member is a musician.

begin_memory_text: We talked briefly about where we live and where we grew up, plus discussed our current families and marriages. We also exchanged names and stated whether or not we had completed similar studies before.
middle_memory_text: We talked about her farm. She told me how many acres of land she lives on and what kind of animals they raise. She also told me a story about the time she tried to save her turkeys from a snake.
end_memory_text: She told me about the novel she is currently writing. She gave me a detailed synopsis and discussed her friends in the creative writing and media fields.
rest_of_day_open: I think I will have a busy week. I have several chores I need to complete. I also have to work the remaining days of the week. I don't see myself being able to rest much, which will likely make me grumpy. But I know I have to accomplish things regardless of my feelings.
critical_positive: We did not interrupt each other. We introduced ourselves without hesitation. We were smiling and friendly towards each other. We discussed a variety of topics. We complimented each other on several points. We were open and honest with each other. We did not really have much in common, but we still got along and had a productive conversation.
critical_negative: She did not allow me to get many words in. She talked quite a bit without giving me a chance to respond or talk about similar experiences in my life. She did not "read the room" to see how I was responding to her- meaning, if she would have, I think she would have allowed response time for me. To be fair, though, she did admit at the beginning that she is a "nervous talker", so I expected most of these things to happen.
